          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="relative">
        <img
          src="/assets/images/=PlateSync-hero.webp"
          alt="Family of four enjoying dinner together, each with their own portion"
          class="w-full rounded-2xl object-cover shadow-lg"
          width="800"
          height="1000"
          loading="eager"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ──── Problem ──── #}
<section class="bg-neutral-50 border-y border-neutral-200">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 md:py-24">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
      <div class="relative order-2 lg:order-1">
        <img
          src="/assets/images/=Platesync-problem.webp"
          alt="Parent staring into an open fridge wondering what to cook for dinner"
          class="w-full rounded-2xl object-cover shadow-md"
          width="800"
          height="533"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-emerald-600 mb-2">The problem</p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900">The weekly scramble stops here</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base text-neutral-600">
          Dad needs 150g of protein. Mum's watching calories. The toddler eats half a serve of everything. The 6-year-old won't touch anything green. You're cooking one meal and somehow everyone needs a different plate — so you default to the same five dinners on repeat.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base text-neutral-600">
          Most meal planners treat your family as one person. PlateSync doesn't.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ──── How It Works ──── #}
<section id="how-it-works" class="bg-white">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 md:py-24">
    <div class="text-center mb-10">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-emerald-600 mb-2">How it works</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900">From setup to shopping list in minutes</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="mb-12">
      <img
        src="/assets/images/=platesync-family-profile.webp"
        alt="Four family member profile cards showing personalised nutrition targets for Mark, Sarah, Leo and Mia"
        class="w-full rounded-2xl object-cover shadow-sm border border-neutral-200"
        width="1200"
        height="600"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      {% set steps = [
        { num: "01", title: "Set up your family", desc: "Add each family member with their age, weight, goals, activity level, allergies, and food preferences. PlateSync calculates personalised daily targets — and adjusts them per day based on each person's training schedule." },
        { num: "02", title: "Build your recipe collection", desc: "Search the web for recipes using AI, or add your own. PlateSync catalogues each recipe with full ingredients, instructions, and per-serving nutrition." },
        { num: "03", title: "Stock your pantry", desc: "Log what's already in your fridge, pantry, and freezer. Type or dictate a list and AI sorts it for you. PlateSync uses this to rank recipes and subtract ingredients from your shopping list." },
        { num: "04", title: "Plan your week", desc: "Assign recipes to each day. The app ranks recipes by what you already have on hand and flags any allergy conflicts. Portions are calculated per person, capped to the recipe's actual serving count." },
        { num: "05", title: "Shop smart", desc: "Confirm your plan and get a shopping list with full-batch ingredient amounts — what you actually buy and cook. Pantry items are subtracted so you only buy what you need." },
        { num: "06", title: "Cook with a guide", desc: "Tap any meal on your phone to open cooking mode: checkable ingredients, step-by-step instructions, and a clear breakdown of how much to plate for each person. No ads, no life story — just the recipe." },
        { num: "07", title: "Handle leftovers", desc: "After cooking, mark the meal as done. Surplus servings? Keep them in the fridge, freeze them, or discard. Leftovers show up as an option for future meals — no extra shopping." }
      ] %}
      {% for step in steps %}
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <span class="font-mono text-sm font-bold text-emerald-600 shrink-0 mt-1">{{ step.num }}</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900">{{ step.title }}</h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">{{ step.desc }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ──── Features ──── #}
<section id="features" class="bg-neutral-50 border-y border-neutral-200">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 md:py-24">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-emerald-600 mb-2">Features</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900">Built for families, not individuals</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      {% set features = [
        { title: "Per-person portions", desc: "Science-backed targets using the Mifflin-St Jeor equation. Protein, calories, and portions personalised for every family member — from toddlers to adults.", img: "/assets/images/=platesync-overhead-dinner-table.webp", imgAlt: "Four plates on a dinner table, each with different portion sizes for different family members" },
        { title: "Day-aware nutrition", desc: "Targets adjust per day based on each person's weekly training schedule. More food on training days, less on rest days.", img: "/assets/images/=platesync-day-aware-nutrition.webp", imgAlt: "Two meal portions side by side — a larger plate for a training day and a smaller plate for a rest day" },
        { title: "Cooking mode", desc: "Full-screen mobile recipe view with checkable ingredients, step-by-step instructions, and per-person portion breakdown. No ads, no life story — just the recipe. Includes child-friendly adaptation notes.", img: "/assets/images/=platesync-feature-highlight.webp", imgAlt: "Hand holding a phone showing a recipe in cooking mode with checkable ingredients" },
        { title: "Leftovers tracking", desc: "Cook the full recipe. Surplus servings are tracked and can be assigned to future meals, frozen, or discarded. Shopping lists skip leftover meals.", img: "/assets/images/=platesync-leftovers-tracking.webp", imgAlt: "Glass meal prep containers stacked in a fridge with portioned meals inside" },
        { title: "Allergy detection", desc: "Recipes are scanned against family members' allergies automatically. Smart enough to know that 'dairy-free milk' isn't dairy.", img: "/assets/images/=Platesync-allergy-detection.webp", imgAlt: "Common allergen foods arranged neatly on a white surface — nuts, dairy, eggs, wheat, shellfish" },
        { title: "Smart shopping lists", desc: "Full-batch ingredient amounts, pantry deduction, and AI normalisation to practical package sizes. Buy what you need, not what a formula says.", img: "/assets/images/=platesync-shopping-list.webp", imgAlt: "Phone showing a shopping list grouped by category with quantities" },
        { title: "AI recipe import", desc: "Search the web for real recipes. AI catalogues every ingredient, every step, and the nutrition — no manual data entry.", img: "/assets/images/=platesync-ai-recipe-import.webp", imgAlt: "Smartphone showing a recipe card interface beside fresh ingredients on a kitchen bench" },
        { title: "Household sharing", desc: "Invite your partner or housemates. Everyone shares recipes, pantry, and meal plans from their own account.", img: "/assets/images/=platesync-household-sharing.webp", imgAlt: "Two smartphones side by side showing the same meal plan, belonging to two different household members" },
        { title: "Supply management", desc: "Track fridge, pantry, and freezer. Type or dictate what you have and AI sorts it instantly. Auto-deducted when you cook, auto-restocked when you shop, restored if you change your mind.", img: "/assets/images/=platesync-supply-management.webp", imgAlt: "Neatly organised kitchen pantry shelf with jars, produce and packaged goods" }
      ] %}
      {% for feature in features %}
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white overflow-hidden">
        {% if feature.img %}
        <img
          src="{{ feature.img }}"
          alt="{{ feature.imgAlt }}"
          class="w-full h-48 object-cover"
          width="600"
          height="400"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        {% endif %}
        <div class="p-5">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900">{{ feature.title }}</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">{{ feature.desc }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ──── FAQ ──── #}
<section id="faq" class="bg-white">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 md:py-24">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-emerald-600 mb-2">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900">Common questions</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="space-y-6">
      {% set faqs = [
        { q: "How does it calculate portions?", a: "It uses the Mifflin-St Jeor equation to calculate daily calorie needs from age, weight, height, sex, and activity level. Protein targets use science-backed ranges (0.9–2.2 g/kg depending on goals). Portions are capped so the total never exceeds the recipe's serving count — you always cook the full batch." },
        { q: "Does it work for kids?", a: "Yes. Child profiles support age-appropriate goals, fussy eater notes, texture aversions, preferred foods, and disliked foods. Kids get appropriately smaller portions based on their actual needs." },
        { q: "What happens to leftovers?", a: "After cooking, you choose what to do with surplus servings: keep in the fridge (4-day expiry), freeze (no expiry), or discard. Leftovers appear as an option when planning future meals — no extra shopping needed." },
        { q: "Do nutrition targets change on training days?", a: "Yes. If a family member has a weekly training schedule (e.g., training Monday, Wednesday, Friday), their calorie and protein targets adjust per day — higher on training days, lower on rest days. Portion tendency (smaller/normal/larger eater) factors in too." },
        { q: "Can I undo a meal if I didn't cook it?", a: "Yes. Cooking mode has a 'Didn't Cook' button that returns all ingredients to your pantry — reversing the deduction from when the plan was confirmed." },
        { q: "What cuisines and diets does it support?", a: "Cuisines include Mediterranean, Asian, Indian, Mexican, Japanese, Korean, Thai, Middle Eastern, American, and African. Diets include balanced, high protein, Mediterranean, keto, paleo, Whole30, vegetarian, and vegan. Each family member can have their own diet preference." },
        { q: "Is my data private?", a: "Yes. All household data is secured with row-level security — only members of your household can access your recipes, pantry, and meal plans. Data is stored on encrypted servers. No personal health data is ever sent to AI providers." },
        { q: "Can multiple people use it?", a: "Yes. The household owner invites members by email. Everyone shares recipes, pantry, meal plans, and family profiles from their own login." },
        { q: "How much does it cost?", a: "PlateSync is currently free during early access. Pricing will be announced soon." }
      ] %}
      {% for faq in faqs %}
      <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-6">
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-neutral-900">{{ faq.q }}</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">{{ faq.a }}</p>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

